Milliseconds allowed before retrying a transmission on the BACnet network if a required acknowledgement is not received.

This is the baud rate presently in use on the MS/TP port. If the device has more than one MS/TP port, this value corresponds to the primary MS/TP port.

Use this table for non-linear inputs not covered by the Sensor Type choices in the Analog Input.
This table plots points on a curve to translate the input units (first column) to engineering units (last column).

NOTE To allow the controller to respond properly if the sensor shorts or opens, the first input unit must be set to zero and the last input unit must be set to a high value, like 1000 kOhms for resistance controllers, or 5 Volts for voltage controllers. (The lowest resistance range allowed on the slidepot is 5 kOhms.)

NOTE Plot more points along the critical section of the curve (room temperature) to improve accuracy. The controller interpolates between the points, so the segments between each point are straight lines.
